p: To get an insight into the chemical profile of A. annua volatile mixtures, the A. annua EO was obtained by steam distillation described above with a yield of 0.18%, which was subsequently submitted to GC-MS analysis. As shown in Table 1, a total of 58 compounds are identified, accounting for 89.39% of the whole EO composition. The principal compound in A. annua EO is camphor (23.48%), followed by germacrene D (9.06%), Î²-caryophyllene (5.39%), and camphene (4.42%), respectively.
